.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
\fI\%MPI_Comm_get_info\fP returns a new info object containing the hints of the
communicator associated with \fIcomm\fP\&. The current setting of all hints
actually used by the system related to this communicator is returned in
\fIinfo_used\fP\&. If no such hints exist, a handle to a newly created info
object is returned that contains no key/value pair. The user is
responsible for freeing info_used via MPI_Info_free\&.
.SH ERRORS
.sp
Almost all MPI routines return an error value; C routines as the value
of the function and Fortran routines in the last argument.
.sp
Before the error value is returned, the current MPI error handler is
called. By default, this error handler aborts the MPI job, except for
I/O function errors. The error handler may be changed with
MPI_Comm_set_errhandler; the predefined error handler MPI_ERRORS_RETURN
may be used to cause error values to be returned. Note that MPI does not
guarantee that an MPI program can continue past an error.
